Key Match Events: Emilio Nsue scored the opening goal for Equatorial Guinea in the ninth minute
William Jebor's shot deflected over the goal for Liberia
Josete Miranda was booked in the 27th minute
Josete Miranda received a second yellow card and was sent off in the 32nd minute
Fede Nguema almost doubled Equatorial Guinea's lead in the 51st minute with a glancing header
Pre-Game Insights: Equatorial Guinea started their Group H campaign with a 1-0 victory against Namibia
Liberia lost their opener 1-0 against the Flames of Malawi
Equatorial Guinea rested Miranda for Fede Nguema and Carlos Akapo for Nestor Senra at halftime
Liberia brought in Daniel Toe for Albert Korvah at halftime
Post-Match Reflections: No post-match reflections available in the article
Miscellaneous Highlights: Equatorial Guinea made it two wins out of two
Liberia's Kenneh was sent off in the 45th minute for a second yellow card
The match was held at the Samuel Kanyon Doe Sports Complex Stadium
